the instructional design team offers a variety of services and expertise to faculty teaching courses at san jose state university. the team assists faculty in designing effective education by continuously evaluating new instructional strategies and technologies for effectiveness, and introducing best practices to enhance the curriculum. instructional designers assist faculty in design and development, training and technology tools, technology support and resources for the development of their courses. yingjie liu lead instructional designer 408-924-2433 yingjie.liu@sjsu.edu ken.anderson@sjsu.edu 408-924-2618 anthony.bolanos@sjsu.edu 408-924-2690 shichen.guo@sjsu.edu 408-924-2290 klaus.trilck@sjsu.edu 408-924-2863 sara.wildman@sjsu.edu phone: 408-924-2337 email: ecampus@sjsu.edu location: irc, room 206 ecampus, irc206 instructional resource center san jose state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0026 